        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="3">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, make sure the engine is in neutral or park, parking brake
                        is set, and wheels are blocked before doing diagnostic or service procedures on engine or
                        vehicle. Read all safety instructions in the SAFETY INFORMATION section of the service manual
                        for this engine.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Make sure the engine has cooled down before removing any components.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain the cooling system into a clean container so coolant can be reused - low enough to
                    remove pipe (approximately 3 gallons).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen upper hose clamp.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0791003" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0791003.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two bolts from the bracket holding the radiator pipe to the front of the
                    engine.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two nuts from the studs that attach the radiator pipe to the thermostat
                    housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0791004" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0791004.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the pipe from the engine taking care to note that there is an O-ring between the
                    pipe and thermostat housing. This O-ring should remain in the groove in the thermostat housing.
                    Sometimes this O-ring will stick to the pipe. If the O-ring is undamaged and can be reused, install
                    it back in the groove in the thermostat housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0791005" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0791005.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="6">
            <title>Reassembly</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install new bracket to the front of the engine reusing the two bolts that were removed
                    with the old pipe. Torque bolts to 34-42 Lbf-ft (47-58 N&#8226;M).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0791006" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0791006.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the nuts on the U-clamp and let it loosely hang in the bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the new pipe through the U-clamp and into the radiator hose.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0791007" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0791007.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 6.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the O-ring is in place in the thermostat housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the radiator pipe down over the studs in the thermostat housing and HAND TIGHTEN
                    the nuts so that the pipe is loose enough to make sure the pipe rests against the clamp on the front
                    of the engine.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the nuts on the U-clamp while making sure that the end of the pipe fits squarely
                    on the thermostat housing and the pipe rests against the bracket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Torque the nuts on the U-clamp to 21-29 Lbf-ft (28-39 N&#8226;M).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0791008" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0791008.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the nuts that hold the radiator pipe to the thermostat housing and torque them
                    to 21-23 Lbf-ft (29-32 N&#8226;M).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0791009" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0791009.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 8.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten the hose clamp on the bottom end of the radiator pipe to 50 inch pounds (6 N&#8226;M).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0791010" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0791010.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure that there is at least 1/2" of clearance between the radiator hose and
                    radiator stay rod.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0791011" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0791011.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 10.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the clean coolant back into the cooling system.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Start the engine and check for leaks.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
